A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Statewide Independent Living Council of Georgia; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Statewide Independent Living Council of Georgia (SILCGA) is a private
4 nonprofit corporation that is governed by people from across the state with all types of
5 disabilities; and
6 WHEREAS, SILCGA was created through amendments to the Rehabilitation Act of 1973,
7 which require states, including Georgia, to establish Statewide Independent Living Councils
8 to provide guidance for the development and expansion of independent living programs; and
9 WHEREAS, the role of SILCGA is to identify any societal barriers to independent living and
10 to collaborate with its Centers for Independent Living, Vocational Rehabilitation Services,
11 and other related entities to remove those barriers and increase supports and needed services;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, SILCGA is also charged with developing the State Plan for Independent Living
14 as required by federal law, and that plan is in place for 2025-2027; and
