15 WHEREAS, SILCGA's Centers for Independent Living, staffed by individuals with
16 disabilities, provide resources to individuals in their communities; and
17 WHEREAS, SILCGA's activities include sponsoring public meetings and hearings for
18 educational and outreach efforts so as to promote and provide information to the public, state
19 agencies, and local organizations as well as to individuals; and
20 WHEREAS, SILCGA also conducts studies and research relevant to the needs of individuals
21 with disabilities; and
22 WHEREAS, SILCGA's mission includes elevating people with disabilities into leadership
23 roles when possible; increasing positive perceptions of people with disabilities; providing
24 information so individuals can be informed and proactive on issues; assuring use of personal
25 assistance services; promoting visitable housing; funding to retrofit housing to become more
26 accessible; advancing accessible public transit; ensuring equal opportunities to education;
27 improving access to quality healthcare and insurance; increasing access to technology; and
28 expanding availability of information sources, including alternative formats and interpreter
29 services.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
31 recognize and commend the Statewide Independent Living Council of Georgia for its service
32 to Georgians living with disabilities and their families.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
34 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Statewide
35 Independent Living Council of Georgia.
